
Machine Learning is used in many real-world applications.
1. Email Spam Detection
Application:
Automatically identifies spam emails.
Example:
	• "You won ₹10 lakh!" → Spam 
	• "Meeting at 10 AM" → Not Spam 
Algorithm Used:
	• Classification 

2. Recommendation Systems
Application:
Recommends products, movies, or songs based on user preferences.
Examples:
	• Netflix recommends movies. 
	• Amazon recommends products. 
	• YouTube recommends videos. 
Algorithm Used:
	• Recommendation algorithms 
	• Classification 

3. House Price Prediction
Application:
Predicts the price of a house based on:
	• Size 
	• Location 
	• Number of bedrooms 
	• Age of the house 
Algorithm Used:
	• Regression 

4. Medical Diagnosis
Application:
Helps doctors detect diseases.
Examples:
	• Diabetes prediction 
	• Heart disease prediction 
	• Cancer detection 
Algorithm Used:
	• Classification 

5. Fraud Detection
Application:
Detects fraudulent banking or credit card transactions.
Example:
If a transaction looks unusual, the system flags it for review.
Algorithm Used:
	• Classification 

6. Face Recognition
Application:
Recognizes people's faces.
Examples:
	• Phone face unlock 
	• Office attendance systems 
Algorithm Used:
	• Deep Learning 

7. Voice Assistants
Application:
Understands voice commands.
Examples:
	• Google Assistant 
	• Siri 
	• Alexa 
Algorithm Used:
	• NLP 
	• Deep Learning 

8. Self-Driving Cars
Application:
Detects roads, traffic signs, vehicles, and pedestrians to assist autonomous driving.
Algorithm Used:
	• Computer Vision 
	• Deep Learning 

9. Customer Churn Prediction
Application:
Predicts which customers are likely to stop using a service.
Examples:
	• Telecom companies 
	• Banks 
	• Subscription services 
Algorithm Used:
	• Classification 

10. Sentiment Analysis
Application:
Determines whether text expresses a positive, negative, or neutral opinion.
Examples:
	• Product reviews 
	• Social media comments 
	• Customer feedback 
Algorithm Used:
	• NLP 

11. Weather Forecasting
Application:
Predicts weather conditions.
Examples:
	• Rain prediction 
	• Temperature forecasting 
Algorithm Used:
	• Regression 
	• Time Series 

12. Chatbots
Application:
Answers customer questions automatically.
Examples:
	• Customer support bots 
	• Banking assistants 
	• AI-powered document assistants 
Algorithm Used:
	• NLP 
	• Large Language Models (LLMs) 
	• RAG (for document-based chatbots)
